subject: More example JUnit code
msgSnippet: Following up on my previous offering of example JUnit code, I have pushed a project called Fraction to GitHub. This implements classic mathematical fractions
messageBody:
Following up on my previous offering of example JUnit code, I have pushed a
project called Fraction to GitHub. This implements classic mathematical
fractions and was written in a test first manner and has documented unit
tests to help those learning JUnit see one style (my style!) of test
implementation.

The code may be found at:

http://github.com/simonpeter/Fraction

I hope that you find it useful.

Simon
(one of the JUnit mailing list moderators)
